cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category because it deals with object representation and detection in natural images. The use of a fully convolutional network and multi-task learning also suggests that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also involves image retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) applications, which further support these categories.
